Patricia Marie Beilman, a daughter of Dr. and Mrs. Robert Lewis Beilman of Madison, Wis., and David Brownlow Poor, a son of Mrs. Daniel Sidney Poor of Ridgewood, N.Y., and Nantucket, Mass., and the late Mr. Poor, were married yesterday at Grace Episcopal Church in New York. The Rev. Kenneth B. Swanson officiated.

Mary Assadi was her sister's matron of honor and Daniel Poor was his brother's best man.

The bride, who will retain her name, is assistant manager of direct marketing businesses at Thomas J. Lipton Inc. in Englewood Cliffs, N.J. She graduated from Carleton College. Her father is an internist at the Dean Clinic in Madison and an associate professor at the University of Wisconsin Medical School.

Mr. Poor, an associate in the New York investment banking firm of Morgan Stanley & Company, is a graduate of the Groton School, Harvard College and Stanford University, where he received a master's degree. His father was an investment banker. He is a great-grandson of Henry William Poor, who with his father, Henry Varnum Poor, established the Poor's Railroad Manual Company, which became Poor's Publishing and merged with Standard Statistics to form Standard & Poor's, the financial information and bond rating company.